FT  01 DEC 92 / Presidential reform urged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BUCHAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
President Francois Mitterrand last night proposed a slight reduction in the
term of French presidents from seven to 'at least 'six years, as part of a
constitutional reform that would also give more power to prime ministers and
more scope for decision by referendum, writes David Buchan in Paris.
But in a letter to France's two parliamentary chambers and constitutional
court, Mr Mitterrand proposed no timetable for the changes and gave no
indication that he intended to apply any reduction in presidential tenure to
himself.
