<TEXT>
STANDARD Chartered yesterday announced the proposed sale of its 50 per cent
stake in Chartered WestLB, the London-based international merchant bank
jointly owned by Standard Chartered and two German banks.
The stake was sold to WestLB (Europe) UK Holdings, which is 75 per cent
owned by Westdeutsche Landesbank and 25 per cent owned by Sudwestdeustsche
