<HEADLINE>
FT  28 NOV 92 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CONTINUED demand for blue chips boosted the JSE all-share index by 37 to
3,134 in steady trading. The gold index added 24 or 3 per cent to 836, while
strong gains in index-linked industrial blue chips lifted that index by 48
to 4,142.
